<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Fake pod shop</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The fastest-growing and most attractive sort o=
f hedge fund these days=C2=A0is the multi-manager =E2=80=9Cpod shop.=E2=80=
=9D These funds=C2=A0hire=C2=A0lots of different portfolio managers running=
 uncorrelated strategies; they monitor the managers closely, minimize direc=
tional market exposure,=C2=A0allocate capital based on performance, and tak=
e=C2=A0capital away rapidly from managers who have=C2=A0losses. The resulti=
ng fund is exactly what big allocators want: The fund offers a steady strea=
m of returns that are not correlated to the market, it has very low risk, a=
nd it is a big stable institution that can manage their money forever.=C2=
=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is such a good model that people keep try=
ing to get into it; we <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/33301955.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbG=
VzLzIwMjMtMTEtMDYvdGhlLXNiZi1jYXNlLXdhcy1lYXN5P2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMDgyM19NT05FW=
VNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIz=
MTEwOCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB53446751" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;">talked on Monday</a>=C2=A0about Bank of New York Mellon=E2=80=99s pl=
ans to get into the pod-shop business. (They plan to distinguish themselves=
 from the leading players by charging lower fees and being nicer to their P=
Ms.)</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But it is also such a good model that people a=
re apparently tempted to=C2=A0<em>fake=C2=A0</em>it. Like, write a business=
 plan hitting the traditional beats =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cwe allocate our=
 capital among a bunch of diverse uncorrelated portfolio managers,=E2=80=9D=
 =E2=80=9Cwe manage risk by pulling=C2=A0capital from PMs who have a big dr=
awdown,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Cwe make money consistently in all markets,=E2=80=
=9D etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0and go out and raise money and then give it all to =
one guy to bet on Bitcoin or whatever. This does not strike me as a <em>goo=
d </em>plan, but here is a US Securities and Exchange Commission <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33301955.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMy0yMzE/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cBcd221273" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;">enforcement action</a> from last week:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securities and Exchange Commission [Thursd=
ay]=C2=A0charged John Hughes, president and chief compliance officer of reg=
istered investment adviser Prophecy Asset Management LP, for his involvemen=
t in a multi-year fraud that concealed losses of hundreds of millions of do=
llars from investors. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">According to the SEC=E2=80=99s complaint, Hugh=
es led investors to believe that their investments were protected from loss=
, telling them the funds=E2=80=99 capital was shared among dozens of sub-ad=
visers who traded in liquid securities and posted cash collateral to offset=
 any trading losses they incurred. In reality, most of the funds=E2=80=99 c=
apital went to one sub-adviser, who incurred massive trading losses that fa=
r exceeded the cash collateral he had contributed. In addition, Hughes caus=
ed the funds to invest in highly illiquid investments, which also resulted =
in substantial losses to the funds. Hughes concealed these losses by fabric=
ating documents and engaging in a series of sham transactions to cover-up t=
he true financial condition of the funds. The complaint also alleges that H=
ughes deceived investors about the diversification and trading strategies i=
n two other funds. By 2020, after losses in funds that Prophecy Asset Manag=
ement managed amounted to more than $350 million, Hughes and Prophecy Asset=
 Management indefinitely suspended redemptions by investors.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is also a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/33301955.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3Yv=
dXNhby1uai9wci9mb3JtZXItdG9wLWV4ZWN1dGl2ZS1pbnZlc3RtZW50LWZ1bmQtYWRtaXRzLTI=
5NC1taWxsaW9uLXNlY3VyaXRpZXMtZnJhdWQtY29uc3BpcmFjeQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cB09ce3de5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;"> federal criminal case</a>; Hughes pleaded guilty to a =
securities fraud conspiracy =E2=80=9Cthat wiped out Prophecy=E2=80=99s fund=
s and caused over $294 million in losses to the victims.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Prophecy not exactly a traditional pod shop: T=
he sub-advisers were not employees, and the protection against drawdowns wa=
s not just =E2=80=9Cwe take away capital from people who lose money=E2=80=
=9D but also =E2=80=9Cthe sub-advisers have to post cash collateral of 10% =
of their allocation, so that if they lose any money they can pay us back.=
=E2=80=9D But it touches on many of=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/33301955.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9maWxlcy9s=
aXRpZ2F0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWludHMvMjAyMy9jb21wLXByMjAyMy0yMzEucGRm/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cBbe5d7e7f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">the same=C2=A0ideas</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Under the Prophecy model, while sub-advisers w=
ere permitted a percentage of profits, they also were also responsible for =
covering losses up to an agreed amount. Typically, PAM required sub-adviser=
s to post 10% of the agreed upon trading allocation as cash collateral to b=
e available to cover possible losses. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The premise of steady, single-digit returns pr=
otected against loss was based on misrepresentations of active risk managem=
ent where sub-advisers were purportedly routinely monitored with respect to=
 diversification, cash collateral, and liquidity of trading strategies. =E2=
=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hughes and Individual 1, through PAM, represen=
ted that Prophecy=E2=80=99s capital was allocated to dozens of sub-advisers=
 employing multiple diverse and even =E2=80=9Cunique=E2=80=9D trading strat=
egies. For example, PAM distributed monthly =E2=80=9Cfact sheets=E2=80=9D t=
o investors stating that Prophecy =E2=80=9Cseeks to generate returns by mak=
ing notional allocations to a diverse group of subadvisers running a variet=
y of discretionary, systematic and unique investment strategies.=E2=80=9D =
=E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hughes and Individual 1, through PAM, distribu=
ted offering and marketing documents that also stated that Prophecy protect=
ed its capital from losses by holding cash collateral contributed by each s=
ub-adviser. PAM represented that if a sub-adviser=E2=80=99s losses absorbed=
 50% or more of its cash collateral deposit, PAM would stop the sub-adviser=
=E2=80=99s trading and require additional collateral or a reduction in expo=
sure.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=99s just that that wasn=E2=80=99t tru=
e. Prophecy allegedly allocated most of its capital to one manager, called =
=E2=80=9CIndividual 2=E2=80=9D in the SEC complaint and =E2=80=9CCo-conspir=
ator-2=E2=80=9D in the criminal one, and covered that up in its investor re=
ports=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cby presenting his total allocation as if Individual 2 w=
ere multiple, individualized sub-advisers.=E2=80=9D (=E2=80=9CSince in or a=
round 2019, Co-conspirator-2 was also the CEO and President of a multi-bill=
ion dollar company that owned and managed large and diversified retail fran=
chises,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3=
3301955.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3YvZDkvMjAyMy0xMS9odWdoZXMuaW5m=
b3JtYXRpb24ucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB19fa6c32" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" =
itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> says the crimi=
nal case</a>; <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3330=
1955.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTE=
