=E2=80=99s Brian Kahn, the=C2=A0chief executive officer of Franchise Group =
Inc., which owns Vitamin=C2=A0Shoppe.)=C2=A0And Prophecy=C2=A0did not actua=
lly have the 10% cash collateral, or even stop the guy out when he had big =
losses:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As of January 2019, Prophecy=E2=80=99s total c=
ash deposit balance equaled a mere 0.77% of the reported gross market value=
 of its assets. By July 2019, Prophecy=E2=80=99s cash deposit balance dippe=
d even lower, to 0.05%.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Prophecy had all but abandoned its cash deposi=
t requirement for Individual 2, notwithstanding Individual 2=E2=80=99s outs=
ized allotment of Prophecy=E2=80=99s trading capital and enormous trading l=
osses.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For instance, Individual 2=E2=80=99s trading l=
osses exceeded the amount of the cash collateral Individual 2 had contribut=
ed by: $55 million in 2018; $216 million in 2019; and $328 million in 2020.=
 ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">From January 2018 through March 2020, Individu=
al 2=E2=80=99s trading losses exceeded the balance of his cash collateral f=
or all but one month.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you lose money every month for two years yo=
u will probably lose your job at a traditional multi-manager fund. But not =
at a fake one!</p>
