"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">multi-manager funds are a good business</a>=E2=
=80=9D:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The rise of multi-manager hedge funds has led =
to a =E2=80=9Cmerry-go-round=E2=80=9D of portfolio managers being offered =
=E2=80=9Csilly=E2=80=9D amounts of money, according to the co-founder of Eu=
rope=E2=80=99s largest hedge fund.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sir Paul Marshall, co-founder of Marshall Wace=
, told an investment conference in Hong Kong on Wednesday the dominance of =
multi-manager platforms had reshaped the industry because they were =E2=80=
=9Cpaying incredible amounts of money to target people=E2=80=9D.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CEverybody wants that Cristiano Ronald=
o on their team, but there aren=E2=80=99t very many Cristiano Ronaldos,=E2=
=80=9D said Marshall, who co-founded the London-based group in 1997 with Ia=
n Wace. =E2=80=9CWhat=E2=80=99s happening is everybody=E2=80=99s getting pa=
id the same as Cristiano Ronaldo.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The particular form of good business here is t=
hat the pass-through fee model at these funds allows them to bill their com=
pensation expense directly to their clients:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Under this model, the manager passes on all co=
sts =E2=80=94 including office rents, technology and data, salaries, bonuse=
s and even client entertainment =E2=80=94 to their end investors. The idea =
is that managers invest heavily in areas such as talent and technology, wit=
h the cost more than offset by resulting performance. They then tend to cha=
rge a 20-30 per cent performance fee on top.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The pass-through model fuels practices such as=
 sign-on bonuses running into millions or tens of millions of dollars, paid=
 sabbaticals and payouts to individual portfolio managers that can be 20 to=
 30 per cent of profits, all of which are designed to lure and retain the t=
op performers.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This creates upward pressure on hedge fund pay=
: If your pay is=C2=A0<em>set=C2=A0</em>by your boss, but=C2=A0<em>paid=C2=
=A0</em>by your clients, there is not a ton of constraint on how high it ca=
n=C2=A0be. It=E2=80=99s not your boss=E2=80=99s money. =E2=80=9CLet=E2=80=
=99s pay you $100 million, bill the clients, and see if they complain,=E2=
=80=9D your boss can say; there is=C2=A0<em>some=C2=A0</em>level at which t=
hey will complain, but apparently nobody has found it yet. Great business.<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Marshall is responding to this pay pressure no=
t only by complaining at conferences but also by passing through some of hi=
s compensation expenses:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The competition for talent has for=
ced traditional hedge fund players such as Marshall=E2=80=99s firm to adapt=
. Its flagship Eureka hedge fund this year added a =E2=80=9Ccompensation su=
rcharge=E2=80=9D worth as much as 0.75 per cent of the fund=E2=80=99s value=
, to be used to reward high performers, a decision Marshall said at the tim=
e was taken because =E2=80=9Cmulti-manager platforms are driving a bidding =
war for talent=E2=80=9D.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=99s like when the Affordable Care Act=
 passed and some restaurants <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/33301955.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucmV1dGVycy5jb20vYXJ0aWNsZS91c2Et=
aGVhbHRoY2FyZS1yZXN0YXVyYW50cy1pZFVLTDFOMExYMUtQMjAxNDAyMjg/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cB92a17f23" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> added a stunt surcharge</a> to customer bill=
s to pay for health insurance; the message was=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cour employee c=
osts have gone up, so we will pass them on to you in a surly showy way.=E2=
=80=9D Only here the cost is not health insurance but competition from Cita=
del.</p>
