<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/33301955.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhlaW5mb3JtYXRpb24uY29tL2FydGlj=
bGVzL2NvYXR1ZS1jdXRzLXZhbHVlLW9mLW9wZW5zZWEtc3Rha2UtYnktOTAtYXMtZnVuZHMtcmV=
0dXJucy1zYWc/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7db3ac4e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Sure</a>!</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One of OpenSea=E2=80=99s biggest i=
nvestors has marked down by 90% its stake in the struggling non-fungible-to=
ken marketplace, implying that the former crypto darling is now valued at $=
1.4 billion or less on paper. Coatue Management, a New York=E2=80=93based h=
edge and venture fund, slashed the value of its $120 million stake in the c=
ompany to $13 million as of the second quarter of this year, according to a=
 document viewed by The Information.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Only $1.4 billion for the leading NFT marketpl=
ace, in 2023, how about that.=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/33301955.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9jcn=
lwdG8tZW50cmVwcmVuZXVycy1hcmUtcGl2b3RpbmctdG8tYWktaGVyZXMtb25lLWZvdW5kZXJzL=
WV4cGVyaWVuY2UtMzRiZTRjNTE_bW9kPWl0cF93c2omcnU9eWFob28/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cB9810b6fa" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;">Elsewhere</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2021, at the height of the investor frenzy =
for crypto startups, entrepreneur Chris Horne raised $2 million in seed fun=
ding for Filta, a marketplace on which customers could buy and sell custom =
nonfungible token face filters that could digitally augment their face, say=
, by adding cat whiskers or a block head. But by the time the company launc=
hed in late summer of 2022, enthusiasm for crypto had waned and Filta was f=
altering.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So Horne pivoted to the new hottest sector: ar=
tificial intelligence. He ditched the NFT idea, and this year relaunched Fi=
lta as a generative AI-powered digital pet, one that talks and can offer it=
s owner emotional support. The technology behind his new company is OpenAI=
=E2=80=99s large language model, ChatGPT. And Horne is running his new Filt=
a venture off the capital he raised for his original concept.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That is probably the most cynical version of =
=E2=80=9Ccrypto guy=C2=A0pivots to AI=E2=80=9D I have ever read, but even h=
ere=C2=A0it=E2=80=99s an obvious improvement. Before, he was going to sell =
people pictures of cats on the blockchain. Now, he is going to sell people =
pictures of cats that will talk and offer emotional support and <em>not=C2=
=A0</em>be on the blockchain. Strictly better!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Oh and elsewhere in =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https:=
//link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33301955.257406/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYnV=
zaW5lc3NpbnNpZGVyLmNvbS9tYXJjLWFuZHJlZXNzZW4taG9yb3dpdHotYWktY29weXJpZ2h0LT=
IwMjMtMTE/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB73ad3abd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsco=
pe=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration=
: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; =
border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">crypto guy=C2=A0pivots=
 to AI</a>=E2=80=9D:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Andreessen Horowitz is warning that billions o=
f dollars in AI investments could be worth a lot less if companies developi=
ng the technology are forced to pay for the copyrighted data that makes it =
work.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The VC firm said AI investments are so huge th=
at any new rules around the content used to train models "will significantl=
y disrupt" the investment community's plans and expectations around the tec=
hnology, according to comments submitted to the US Copyright Office.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">"The bottom line is this," the firm, known as =
a16z, wrote. "Imposing the cost of actual or potential copyright liability =
on the creators of AI models will either kill or significantly hamper their=
 development."</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If I were a science fiction writer I would be =
working on a story about=C2=A0venture capitalists=C2=A0building a runaway a=
rtificial intelligence that will likely enslave or destroy humankind, only =
to be=C2=A0thwarted by a minor poet suing them for copyright violations for=
 scraping her poems. <em>Terminator: Fair Use Doctrine.=C2=A0</em>What if f=
astidious enforcement of intellectual property rights is all that stands be=
tween us and annihilation by robots?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">More generally, you could have a regulatory mo=
del that is like:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Nobody will ever again write=C2=A0tho=
ughtful or productive regulations for anything.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-=
bottom: 5px;">Occasionally the unintended consequences of other, older regu=
lations will accidentally stop the worst features of some new, impossible-t=
o-regulate-thoughtfully thing.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Is US crypto regulation like that? Yes? Is AI-=
regulation-by-copyright like that? No, I am just being silly, but what if i=
t was?</p>
